<div class="inline-f6d8c6e93a">
        The <strong>IEEE International Symposium on Smart Electronic Systems (IEEE iSES 2025)</strong> invites proposals for the <strong>Student Research Forum (SRF)</strong>. This forum offers an opportunity for recently graduated or currently enrolled third/final year B.Tech/M.Tech/MCA/Ph.D. students to present their thesis or project work to a wide audience from academia and industry.
      </div>
<br/>
<div class="inline-f6d8c6e93a">
        The SRF is a unique platform to showcase innovative work in the following domains:
      </div>
<ul class="inline-f6d8c6e93a">
<li>Nanoelectronic, VLSI and Sensor Systems (NVS)</li>
<li>Energy-Efficient, Reliable VLSI Systems (ERS)</li>
<li>Hardware/Software for the Internet of smart Things and Healthcare (IoTH)</li>
<li>Hardware for Secure Information Processing (SIP)</li>
<li>Hardware/Software Solutions for AI &amp; Big Data (SAB)</li>
<li>Cyber Physical Systems and Social Networks (CSN)</li>
</ul>
<div class="inline-f6d8c6e93a">
        Industry and academic professionals will get a glimpse into emerging innovations from the next generation of researchers in Smart Electronics.
      </div>
<br/>
<div class="inline-378e240f4a">
        Eligibility:
      </div>
<div class="inline-f6d8c6e93a">
<ul class="inline-7d27179924">
<li>Open to Ph.D. students or final/third-year B.Tech/M.Tech/MCA students currently engaged in research.</li>
<li>Research topics must be relevant to the Smart Electronics domain.</li>
<li>Repeat SRF presenters must ensure at least 70% new technical content compared to their previous submission.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<br/>
<div class="inline-378e240f4a">
        Submission Guidelines:
      </div>
<div class="inline-7d27179924">
        Authors must submit a short paper (2–4 pages) in IEEE double-column conference format that includes:
        <ul class="inline-7d27179924">
<li>Title, Authors, and Affiliations</li>
<li>Abstract</li>
<li>Introduction and Motivation</li>
<li>Proposed Design</li>
<li>Conclusions and References</li>
</ul>
<ul class="inline-7d27179924">
<li>The first author must be a student.</li>
<li>Submit a single PDF through the <a href="https://cmt3.research.microsoft.com/IEEEiSeS2025">Microsoft CMT</a> system.</li>
<li>All submissions will undergo peer review.</li>
<li>Accepted papers will be published in the official IEEE conference proceedings (IEEE Xplore).</li>
</ul>
</div>
<br/>
<div class="inline-378e240f4a">
        Benefits to Selected Researchers:
      </div>
<div class="inline-7d27179924">
<ul class="inline-7d27179924">
<li>4-page publication in IEEE iSES 2025 proceedings (IEEE Xplore indexed)</li>
<li>Presentation in the SRF session</li>
<li>Networking opportunities with industry and academic leaders</li>
<li>Travel grants for student first authors of accepted submissions</li>
<li>Encouragement for submissions that demonstrate innovation and strong use cases</li>
</ul>
</div>
